        <detaileddescription>
<para>Recursively scans the current matrix, to build tree of parent voxels using the contents of the sparase matrix to indicate connectivity. Emits warning noises and returns an empty vector if the entire tree cannot be traversed, or if the current matrix is not tree-like. Assumes row 0 is root row. User should always call with parentRow == 0; Doesn&apos;t work yet. bool buildTree( unsigned int parentRow,
        vector&lt; unsigned int &gt;&amp; parentVoxel ) const; Reduces the forward elimination phase into a series of operations defined by the fops vector.</para>
<para>Builds the vector of forward ops: ratio, i, j RHS[i] = RHS[i] - RHS[j] * ratio This vec tells the routine which rows below have to be eliminated. This includes the rows if any in the tridiagonal band and also rows, if any, on branches. </para>
